   PURPOSE
   =======

     This document will describe the services  rendered  by  the  Network 
     Systems  Support  Center  (NSSC)  to  customers  utilizing BT  North
     America  private  networks,  hybrid  networks and subnetworks.  





   OVERVIEW
   ========

     The Network Systems Support Center provides three distinct services.  
     It  acts  as  a  customer  service  organization;  it  also provides 
     personnel  to   operate  and   monitor   private  networks,   hybird
     networks  and  subnetworks;  and   it   provides   line   management
     services.  Although the  Network Systems  Support  Center  has  many 
     responsibilities,  its  primary mission is  to guarantee the quality
     of service that is extended to the users of private networks, hybrid 
     networks and subnetworks.  

     The specific services provided by the Network Systems Support Center 
     are  listed  below and are grouped according to the three basic NSSC 
     functions.  









 






      Customer Services
      -----------------

      * Accept trouble reports.
      * Maintain trouble tickets on reported problems.
      * Perform brief initial investigation of problem.
      * Attempt to resolve the problem.
      * Obtain hardware/software support if required.
      * Track problem when turned over to hardware/software support.
      * Verify with customer that service is restored after corrective
          action has been taken.
      * Enforce technical escalations.
      * Open tickets for Preventive Maintenance.
      * Make managerial escalations within the various Support Groups as 
          required to guarantee quality of service.
      * Make trouble tickets available via the network(s) for customer
          inspection and for customers to status their tickets.
      * Provide Availability/Overload Reports to those customers
          who have TMCS and who subscribe to the service.
      * Open and track Non-OES Project Tickets.
   











